# Data Layer

## Entities (Remote / Domain / UI)

Always three separate layers:

| Layer         | Location                          | Purpose                               |
|---------------|-----------------------------------|---------------------------------------|
| RemoteEntity  | `impl/data/network/`              | DTO for serialization (Ktor/JSON)     |
| DomainEntity  | `api/models/`                     | Business entity                       |
| UiEntity      | `presentation/models/`            | UI model (formatted data)             |

All models are **separate files** in `model/` (`models/`) folders at each layer. Nested data classes inside Store are **forbidden** — models are always top-level.

Rules:
- Repository **always** returns Domain entities
- Remote → Domain mapping happens inside the Repository implementation
- Domain → UI mapping happens in the Presentation mapper
- **Forbidden** to pass Remote entities above the data layer

## Mapper

All mapping via mapper classes (`common/mappers/Mapper.kt`):

```kotlin
interface Mapper<From, To> {
    fun map(item: From): To
    fun map(list: List<From>): List<To> = list.map { item -> map(item) }
}
```

Each mapper is a separate interface + implementation, injected via Koin.

```kotlin
// Interface
internal interface ItemMapper : Mapper<RemoteItem, DomainItem>

// Implementation
internal class ItemMapperImpl : ItemMapper {
    override fun map(item: RemoteItem): DomainItem = with(item) {
        DomainItem(
            id = id,
            title = title,
            isActive = isActive ?: false,
        )
    }
}
```

## Remote Entities (DTO)

Rules:
- `@Serializable` is required
- `@SerialName` is required on **every** field, even if the name matches the JSON key
- **No default parameters** — if a field may be absent in JSON, the type must be nullable (`Type?`)
- All fields are `val`

```kotlin
@Serializable
internal data class RemoteItem(
    @SerialName("id") val id: String,
    @SerialName("title") val title: String,
    @SerialName("is_active") val isActive: Boolean?,
)
```

## Domain → UI Mappers (presentation layer)

Location: `presentation/mappers/`

**StateMapper:**

```kotlin
interface Ui{Feature}StateMapper {
    fun map(state: {Feature}Store.State): Ui{Feature}State
}

internal class Ui{Feature}StateMapperImpl : Ui{Feature}StateMapper {

    override fun map(state: {Feature}Store.State): Ui{Feature}State = with(state) {
        Ui{Feature}State(
            value = someValue,
            isLoading = isLoading,
        )
    }
}
```

**LabelMapper:**

```kotlin
interface Ui{Feature}LabelMapper : Mapper<{Feature}Store.Label, Ui{Feature}Label>

internal class Ui{Feature}LabelMapperImpl : Ui{Feature}LabelMapper {

    override fun map(item: {Feature}Store.Label): Ui{Feature}Label = when (item) {
        {Feature}Store.Label.NavigateToNext -> Ui{Feature}Label.NavigateToNext
    }
}
```

## Mapping Rules

- All mapping via classes: **interface** (public) + **internal implementation**
- Interface extends `Mapper<From, To>`
- Implementation is always `internal class`
- Mappers are injected via Koin (never instantiated directly)
- A mapper may depend on other mappers (composition via injection)
- Remote entities **never leave** the data layer
- Repository always returns only domain entities
- Private helper `toUi()` extension functions are acceptable **inside** a mapper class
